1. Install Thonny

Download from thonny.org
.

Thonny comes with its own bundled Python (beginner-friendly).

2. Check interpreter

Open Thonny → Tools → Options → Interpreter.

Make sure it points to your desired Python version (Bundled or System).

3. Install packages inside Thonny

In menu: Tools → Manage Packages…

Search for requests → Install.

Search for pillow → Install.

4. Create your script

File → New → Paste this code:

import requests
from io import BytesIO
from PIL import Image

url = "https://picsum.photos/300"
resp = requests.get(url)
resp.raise_for_status()

img = Image.open(BytesIO(resp.content))
img.save("downloaded.jpg")
print("✅ Image saved")


Save as app.py.

5. Run it

Press the green Run button (▶).

Check your working folder (bottom right status bar shows path).

You should see downloaded.jpg.
